	<h1>London After Midnight</h1>
</header>

	<section id="film-detail-container">
		<img src="../static/images/m04.jpeg" alt="Film poster">

		<p><em>London After Midnight</em> is a silent mystery horror film directed by Tod Browning, starring Lon Chaney, Marceline Day, Conrad Nagel, Henry B. Walthall, Polly Moran, Edna Tichenor, and Claude King.</p>

		<p>Tod Browning and Irving Thalberg produced the film.</p>

		<p>
			It was released by Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer on December 3, 1927, with a runtime of 69 minutes.

			
				It had a budget of $151,666  and made $1 million at the box office.
				When adjusted for inflation in 2023, that's approximately equivalent to $2.6 million and $17.2 million, respectively.
			
		</p>

		<p>
			The film was written by Waldemar Young and Joseph W. Farnham (titles), with Sam Feinburg and Jack Feinburg composing the filmâ€™s music. Merritt B. Gerstad oversaw cinematography, and Harry Reynolds and Irving Thalberg (uncredited) helped with editing the film.
		</p>

		<p><a href="lost">View an archived version of <em>London After Midnight</em>.</a></p>

